[[<]]
[[div class="darkpanel storm large thin"]]
[[span class="bd"]]SP CIAL  ONTAINME T PROC  URES[[/span]] 
----
@@ @@
[[size 70%]]{{cannot access memory address 0xff3fffd8}}[[/size]] 
@@ @@
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="darkpanel storm large thin" style="position:relative;"]]
[[span class="bd"]] REVISED SPECIAL CONTAINMENT PROCEDURES[[/span]] 
----
Due to the nature of the anomaly, containment is unnecessary.[[footnote]]**Tangent:** The effects of the anomaly are theoretically extreme, but would not be recognized as such.[[/footnote]]

Despite this, the scope of anomalous influence presented should not be understated.[[footnote]]**Antiabsentia:** Anomaly is employed by nonexistent phenomena in ensuring the presence of the Foundation.
@@ @@
**Systemic:** Anomaly is capable of affecting the entire Database.
[[/footnote]]

Any documentation of interest to the [[[deleted|Department of Deletions]]] should be preserved via the "ACCUMULUS" backup system, which ensures redundancy for data integrity in the event of unanticipated whiteout events. The system’s recursive archival protocols allow for limited reconstruction of overwritten sectors from a temporary storage cache in the event this system fails, however, the anomaly's unpredictable behavior and the instability of data produced this way often renders such efforts unproductive.[[footnote]]**Ictus:** Anomaly has stochastic improbability; therefore, forecasting its occurrence is unlikely.[[/footnote]]  

Thus, SCP-{{NaN}} is instead subjected to //access restriction procedures// and //response protocol//, as outlined below. 
[[span style="top:3px; right:5px; position:absolute;"]][[size 50%]]//{{preserved via 'ACCUMULUS' backup system}}//[[/size]][[/span]]
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="darkpanel storm large thin" style="position:relative;"]]
[[span class="bd"]]ACCESS RESTRICTION PROCEDURES[[/span]]
----
SCP-{{NaN}}-ALPHA instances are to be treated as hazardous null-type entities. No Deletions personnel, especially those assigned to sectoral maintenance of volatile datasets, are permitted to acknowledge or interact with SCP-{{NaN}} under standard operating directives.

In the event any emergent components or affected memory regions become unstable, implicated personnel are to immediately reference this document’s protected segments. Personnel are to observe affected instances closely and provide verbal reinforcement of their current spatial coordinates. Communication should be concise and directive; affected instances are encouraged to “wait for processing” until the anomaly’s response concludes. __**There will be no remains.**__

Under [[span class="bd"]]OPERATION FIREWALL[[/span]], the deployment of ALG-{{NaN}} for personal use is strictly prohibited. Noncompliance will result in reconstruction and indefinite contract extension, enforced under the Department of Deletions' personnel retention clause. 
[[span style="top:3px; right:5px; position:absolute;"]][[size 50%]]//{{preserved via 'ACCUMULUS' backup system}}//[[/size]][[/span]]
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="darkpanel storm large thin" style="position:relative;"]]
[[span class="bd"]]RESPONSE PROTOCOL[[/span]]
----
Segments related to Response Protocols should remain obfuscated for security purposes, accessible only under Level [[span style="transform:rotate(180deg);"]]⟁[[/span]]/{{NaN}} authorization. Collapse this section immediately upon review.
[[span style="top:3px; right:5px; position:absolute;"]][[size 50%]]//{{preserved via 'ACCUMULUS' backup system}}//[[/size]][[/span]]
[[/div]]
[[/<]]
@@ @@
